https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#description:
Aggregate crop supply response model. Based on the Agricultural Sample Survey reports (AgSS), two crops are harvested in this region: maize and sorghum, so this model includes only 2 crops. Land use, production and yield level data comes from Agss report 2014 (http://surveys.worldbank.org/lsms/programs/integrated-surveys-agriculture-ISA/ethiopia)

The price index still comes from the World Food Programme report, which included Gambella and its own set of prices.

The Nitrogen application rate is set to a low value because farmers in Gambella utilize very low level of fertilizer.  
All other parameters, have been approximate based the South Sudan model calibration.
https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#keywords: economy; land use; crop production; fertilizer costs
https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#hasAssumption: The model assumes that only one parameter will be adjusted at the same time

A basic configuration of the TopoFlow model (v36-2.1.0) aggregating al inputs as a zip file and allowing changing precipitation rates and start/end and time stamp for simulation
https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#hasUsageNotes:
This Topoflow configuration has ISRIC with data for 7 soil layers, and using data from the top 3.
The start and end dates must be compatible with the data selected. For example, if the data is from 2017 the start date cannot be 2018"

There is a 'CHECK_STABILITY' flag that you can set in some of the input configuration files (channels_kin_wave and infil_richards_1d). Since there is no way to predict stable time step size in advance, we have calculated it by trial and error to find the largest value that makes the model work. Once this value is set up, the CHECK_STABILITY flag may be switched to 'No' to speed up the execution of the model. The vertical spacing in the infiltration component (set via dz and nz) layers needs to be small to handle a wide range of rainfall values, but this means the timestep (dt) also needs to be smaller to keep the model stable
https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#keywords: snowmelt;precipitation;evapotranspiration;infiltration;channel/overland flow;shallow subsurface flow;flow diversions

https://w3id.org/okn/o/sd#hasUsageNotes:
This Topoflow configuration has ISRIC with data for 7 soil layers, and using data from the top 3.

There is a 'CHECK_STABILITY' flag that you can set in some of the input configuration files (channels_kin_wave and infil_richards_1d). Since there is no way to predict stable time step size in advance, we have calculated it by trial and error to find the largest value that makes the model work. Once this value is set up, the CHECK_STABILITY flag may be switched to 'No' to speed up the execution of the model. The vertical spacing in the infiltration component (set via dz and nz) layers needs to be small to handle a wide range of rainfall values, but this means the timestep (dt) also needs to be smaller to keep the model stable.
